There are WAY more of these cretins in America  than any other country. That why most other nation's derisively refer to America as the 'excited states.' The combination of 350 millions guns owned by excitable, in some cases unstable, people  causes countless instances of people trying to solve interpersonal problems by shooting the other person. Canadians are more reserved, ad ha about a third as much gun violence as America per capita. British citizens are ever more reserved, and have even less gun violence. Well, until NRA's grip on half of America's elected representatives' balls is broken, little will get done except for the ban on bump stocks. Clearly reform of corporate lobbying is badly needed. If you feel you're being wronged, there is legal recourse available through the courts and arbitration panels. If detained by police, keep your mouth shut and your eyes and ears open. Granted no American has a constitutional right to drive drunk, as they do to bear armsbut the point is valid nonetheless. \n\nIt will take a long, sustained effort over at least four or five US Administrations to significantly reduce gun deaths and violencebut it is worth it.
